Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: The Hall of Prayer for Good Harvests in the Temple of Heaven
Description: A circular temple first built in 1420, where emperors of the Ming and Qing Dynasty held the Heaven Worship Ceremony.

Name: The American Museum of Natural History in New York
Description: This museum complex contains 45 exhibition halls, a planetarium and a library. Fun fact: the movie Night at the Musem is based on this museum, and incorporated exterior shots in the film.

Name: The Steamboat Geyser in Yellowstone National Park
Description: This geyser is the world's tallest currently-active geyser. Though I only saw a minor eruption of appr. 15 ft, major eruptions can throw water more than 300 ft in the air.

Name: Radcliffe Camera in Oxford University
Description: This building in the heart of Oxford was originally built to house the Radcliffe Science Library. Fun fact: J.R.R. Tolkein once suggested that the building resembles Sauron's temple to Morgoth.

Name: The National Historical Museum of Brazil
Description: This museum, created in 1922, has more than 25 exhibits, and hosts a collection of over 287,000 items
